# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have to Output the list of Players who lost  0 matches or 1 matches and should've played atleast 1 match.
So we can use Map to find the number of matches won by particular player and another Map to store the number of matches lost by a player.
And then iterating through map we can find the answer.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can create 1 map to store the Winners and the number of the matches they won(frequency) and 2 map for players and the matches they lost.
For finding the players who lost 0 matches we can select players from 1st list and look if they are present in the map2 (where losers are stored) then that player can't be included in the list 1 else we include them in the list 1.
For finding the players who lost 1 match we can just look in 2nd Map for players whose frequency is 1(they lost only 1 match) and include that players in list 2.
Lastly we combine and return both lists.
Hope you Understand!

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
**O((log(n))^2)**
 <!--  -->
For iterating in map1 and using find() function both having log(n) complexity.
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
**O(n)**
