# Intuition
Eliminate a person after every k turns until a single person is left.
n and k have really small values. Simply simulate the process.

# Approach
- Create a queue which initially contains numbers from 1 to n.
- For k-1 times, shift the first element of the queue to the end of the queue and pop the element from queue at the kth turn.
- Do above step until queue have only 1 element left which is the required answer.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n*k)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

